00:40:11.760 --> 00:40:15.460
Cauchy's rigidity theorem here
and say, oh, this uniquely

00:40:15.460 --> 00:40:19.390
assembles into this
spiky tetrahedron.

00:40:19.390 --> 00:40:22.480
You could, in principle,
drawn an across here

00:40:22.480 --> 00:40:23.889
with the appropriate gluing.

00:40:23.889 --> 00:40:25.680
It's a little tricky
to draw in because you

00:40:25.680 --> 00:40:27.270
have to also triangulate.

00:40:27.270 --> 00:40:30.010
It'd be hard to do from
scratch to compute gluings.

00:40:30.010 --> 00:40:32.210
But in theory, especially
if you use software

00:40:32.210 --> 00:40:34.001
to compute the gluings
and compute shortest

00:40:34.001 --> 00:40:36.820
path in a glued
polygon-- which we'll

00:40:36.820 --> 00:40:38.680
